## auto-gdd monorepo

Local AI GDD generator. Offline-only. Never add cloud API calls.

### Package layout
- `packages/core` — all shared logic (Ollama, RAG, GDD assembler). No CLI/UI deps.
- `packages/cli` — `npx auto-gdd` terminal interface
- `packages/mcp` — MCP server (Stdio) for Cursor/Claude/Windsurf
- `packages/vscode` — VS Code/Cursor extension (CommonJS — required by VS Code API)

### Non-negotiable rules
- **Offline only.** No `openai`, `anthropic`, `groq`, or any cloud AI SDK. Use `OllamaClient` in `packages/core/src/ollama/`.
- **Build after every `.ts` edit.** A `postToolUse` hook runs `npm run build` automatically and surfaces errors.
- **ESM everywhere except `packages/vscode`**, which must stay CommonJS for the VS Code extension API.
- **Import paths must include `.js` extension** (Node16 module resolution). ESLint enforces this.

### Where things live
| Concern | File |
|---------|------|
| GDD section prompts | `packages/core/src/gdd/PromptTemplates.ts` |
| Game engine profiles | `packages/core/src/engines/engineProfiles.ts` |
| Engine auto-detection | `packages/core/src/detector/WorkspaceDetector.ts` |
| Config read/write | `packages/core/src/config/ConfigStore.ts` |
| Vector store | `.auto-gdd-vectors/` (vectra, file-based, no server) |

### Adding a new engine
1. Add to `ENGINE_PROFILES` in `engineProfiles.ts`
2. Add signature to `RULES` array in `WorkspaceDetector.ts`
3. Add detection in `.cursor/hooks/workspace-open.js`
